<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Isocoma</i> <i>acradenia</i> or <i>Suaeda</i> <i>moquinii</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub layer with <i>Allenrolfea</i> <i>occidentalis</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>canescens</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>polycarpa</i>, <i>Kochia</i> <i>californica</i> and <i>Sarcobatus</i> <i>vermiculatus</i>. Herbs may include <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Schismus</i> spp. or <i>Sporobolus</i> <i>airoides</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1.5 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Suaeda moquinii</i> > 2% absolute cover and no other shrub ≥ cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b, VegCAMP and AIS 2013, Buck-Diaz and Evens 2012).</li>
		
		<li><i>Suaeda moquinii</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy or > 30% relative cover when co-dominant with <i>Atriplex canescens</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2012, Evens et al. 2014)</li>
		
		<li><i>Isocoma acradenia</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous layer as a perennial herb or sub-shrub with variable cover.  It may be co-dominant with other herbs including <i>Bromus</i> spp., <i>Frankenia salina, Hordeum</i> spp. And <i>Lepidium dictyotum</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2013).</li>
		
		<li><i>Isocoma acradenia</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Buck-Diaz and Evens 2012, Evens et al. 2014).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Flat to gently sloping valley bottoms, playas, toe slopes adjacent to alluvial fans, and bajadas. Soils are deep; saline or alkaline. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (2012 national list) recognizes <i>Suaeda moquinii</i> as a OBL plant and <i>Isocoma acradenia </i>as a FACU plant. </div>
</div>

        
